    "body": "Can you give specific examples of where the plot needs to be updated? I don't think we are using much hard-coded style elements in the plot method.\r\n\r\nIf you are talking about the documentation (http://pandas.pydata.org/pandas-docs/stable/visualization.html), we are already using the `style` support of matplotlib, but using the 'ggplot' style instead of the default (but that is just for the docs, not for the default that users get when plotting). So for this, we could indeed switch to the default style again now this has been improved. "
